Setting Up a Virtual Environment

Installation
It's recommended to use a virtual environment for your project to manage dependencies. To set one up:

Install virtualenv:
bash
Copy code
pip install virtualenv
Creation and Activation
After installing virtualenv, navigate to your project directory in the terminal or command prompt:

Create a virtual environment named 'venv':
bash
Copy code
virtualenv venv
Activate the virtual environment:
Windows:
bash
Copy code
.\venv\Scripts\activate
macOS and Linux:
bash
Copy code
source venv/bin/activate
Installing Required Libraries

Once inside the virtual environment, install the necessary libraries:

Install Google Cloud libraries:
bash
Copy code
pip install --upgrade google-cloud-speech google-cloud-translate
Install the Transformers library:
bash
Copy code
pip install transformers
Install SpaCy and its English language model:
bash
Copy code
pip install spacy
python -m spacy download en_core_web_sm